### **TL;DR: Everything You Need to Know About Radiant Cut Diamonds**

A radiant cut diamond is a square or rectangular brilliant-cut diamond with clipped (beveled) corners and 70 facets designed to reflect light from every angle — making it one of the most brilliant of all rectangular diamonds. It is the only diamond shape that applies full brilliant-cut faceting to both the crown and pavilion in a rectangular outline — delivering the intense sparkle of a round brilliant in the geometric silhouette of an emerald cut.

**Live 2026 price snapshot:**

-   1ct natural H-VS2 Very Good Cut IGI (best value): **[$1,910](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26737014?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   1ct natural E-VVS1 Ideal Cut GIA: **[$4,560](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28879187?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   1ct natural D-VVS1 Ideal Cut GIA: **[$4,650](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29067559?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   1.30ct natural D-IF Very Good Cut GIA (top specs): **[$10,950](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27980222?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   1.50ct natural H-VS2 Very Good Cut GIA (largest carat): **[$6,980](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27623999?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

**The one thing every radiant buyer must know:** GIA does not issue a cut grade for radiant cut diamonds. "Ideal Cut" and "Very Good Cut" on Blue Nile listings are retailer assessments — not laboratory certifications. Every radiant cut purchase requires manual proportion verification from the GIA certificate.

**Buy a radiant cut if:**

-   You want the maximum sparkle and fire of any rectangular or square diamond
-   You want the geometric outline of an emerald cut without sacrificing brilliance
-   You want clipped corners that eliminate princess cut chipping risk while maintaining angular geometry
-   You want a growing trend shape — radiant cut diamonds have rapidly become a centerpiece of 2025 and 2026 jewelry trends

**Consider a different shape if:**

-   You want the maximum apparent size per dollar — oval and marquise deliver more face-up area
-   You want the hall-of-mirrors step-cut aesthetic — emerald cut is the answer
-   You want a soft, vintage-romantic outline — cushion cut with rounded corners
-   You are on the tightest budget — cushion and princess are cheaper

