tional fire of a radiant’s 70 facets acts as a natural camouflage system for tiny crystal flaws. Unlike step-cut emerald diamonds that demand high clarity tiers, a radiant lets you safely step down to a VS2 or clean SI1 tier with zero visual loss, freeing up major budget.</td></tr><tr class="highlight-row"><td><strong>Color sensitivity</strong></td><td>Moderate — H or better in white metal</td><td><strong>8/10 — The Body Mass Trap.</strong> The deep, concentrated pavilion layout of a radiant acts like a prism that naturally concentrates body tint. For crisp platinum or white gold settings, keeping your selection at an H grade or higher prevents noticeable warmth from dulling your face-up presentation.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Durability</strong></td><td>Excellent — clipped corners eliminate chipping risk</td><td><strong>10/10 — Bulletproof Architectural Design.</strong> Unlike princess cuts that feature fragile, sharp 90-degree points prone to shearing under pressure, the radiant's cropped corners disperse mechanical impact forces beautifully. This structural design makes it an ideal, worry-free option for active daily wear.</td></tr><tr class="highlight-row"><td><strong>Bow-tie risk</strong></td><td>Possible in elongated versions — evaluate on video</td><td><strong>7/10 — Geometric Hazard Zone.</strong> While square variations remain completely clean and uniform, pushing the length-to-width ratio past 1.30 creates an optical challenge. An elongated outline introduces the risk of a dark central bow-tie shadow, making a high-resolution 4K video or hands-on audit mandatory.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Trending direction</strong></td><td>Growing rapidly through 2026 with radiant pendants forecasted as one of the biggest gifting trends</td><td><strong>9/10 — Cultural Style Momentum.</strong> The radiant cut’s sharp aesthetic trajectory is moving far beyond bridal profiles. In mid-2026, its clean-lined border and fierce brilliance have established it as a major favorite for custom high-end drop pendants, securing its place as a top-tier luxury design asset.</td></tr></tbody></table>

